WebComponents.ScrollHost.Title=Why PhialeWebComponentScrollHost exists
WebComponents.ScrollHost.Description=This host keeps WebView2CompositionControl inside a clipped, style-driven viewport so desktop overlays can stay native while scroll no longer depends on WPF ScrollViewer.
WebComponents.ScrollHost.PointOne=It protects keyboard focus for Monaco and other browser-hosted editors by keeping the scroll container out of tab order.
WebComponents.ScrollHost.PointTwo=It clips the browser surface to the viewport, so the hosted content does not bleed outside cards, dialogs or shell regions.
WebComponents.ScrollHost.PointThree=It stays style-sensitive through the shared style library, so scrollbar chrome and container appearance follow the app theme instead of local hardcoded values.
