Example.Grouping.Title=Grouping
Example.Grouping.Description=Drag the Category column header into the grouping surface, reorder the active groups and remove them again.
Example.ApplicationStateManager.Title=ApplicationStateManager
Example.ApplicationStateManager.Description=Persists user-owned UI overlays such as grid layout, sorting, filters and other view state, but never the base definition itself.
Example.DefinitionManager.Title=DefinitionManager
Example.DefinitionManager.Description=Resolves the base definition for a page or component, explains where it came from and leaves user-owned UI state to ApplicationStateManager.
Example.WebHost.Title=Web Host
Example.WebHost.Description=Shows the reusable browser host with ready-state tracking, .NET to JS messaging and a shared runtime that higher-level controls can build on.
Example.PdfViewer.Title=PdfViewer
Example.PdfViewer.Description=Shows a reusable PDF viewer with a native toolbar, file-backed document loading, search, zoom and print on top of the neutral WebHost.
Example.ReportDesigner.Title=ReportDesigner
Example.ReportDesigner.Description=Shows a reusable report designer with native shell controls, JSON-backed preview data and browser-hosted design and print surfaces on top of the neutral WebHost.
Example.MonacoEditor.Title=MonacoEditor
Example.MonacoEditor.Description=Shows a reusable Monaco code editor wrapped in a native shell and mounted through the neutral WebHost with offline Monaco assets.
Example.WebComponentScrollHost.Title=PhialeWebComponentScrollHost
Example.WebComponentScrollHost.Description=Shows the dedicated scroll host that keeps WebView2CompositionControl clipped, style-driven and out of keyboard focus so browser editors can still type normally.
Example.MyLicense.Title=My license
Example.MyLicense.Description=Reserved placeholder for the product or company license text that will be added later.
Example.ThirdPartyLicenses.Title=Third-party licenses
Example.ThirdPartyLicenses.Description=Lists the open-source notices and local license files required by the bundled PdfViewer and ReportDesigner web assets.
Example.Foundations.Title=Preview foundations
Example.Foundations.Description=Maps the typography roles, semantic brushes, surfaces and repeated layout constants already used by the current demo shell.
Example.Filtering.Title=Filtering
Example.Filtering.Description=Type into the filter boxes to narrow municipalities, owners, statuses and geometry records without leaving the current view.
Example.Sorting.Title=Sorting
Example.Sorting.Description=Click GIS attribute headers to sort by category, inspection date or geometry metrics, and use Shift plus click to build a multi-column chain.
Example.Summaries.Title=Summaries
Example.Summaries.Description=Shows live totals for area and length plus object counts that follow the current filtered GIS result set.
Example.ColumnLayout.Title=Column Layout
Example.ColumnLayout.Description=Demonstrates resizing, reordering, freezing and toggling wide GIS attribute columns on the live surface.
Example.Selection.Title=Selection
Example.Selection.Description=Highlights multi-cell selection, active cell tracking and clipboard copy support across GIS feature records.
Example.Editing.Title=Editing
Example.Editing.Description=Turns on inline editing for mutable metadata such as object name, status, priority and owner.
Example.Constraints.Title=Constraints
Example.Constraints.Description=Demonstrates declarative field constraints for text, code, lookup, date, integer and decimal columns with live validation feedback while typing.
Example.RichEditors.Title=Rich Editors
Example.RichEditors.Description=Shows combo, date picker, autocomplete and masked text editors on live GIS metadata columns so each value type uses an intentional editor.
Example.State.Title=State Persistence
Example.State.Description=Save the current GIS layout, sorting, filters and grouping, then restore them on demand.
Example.Remote.Title=Remote Data
Example.Remote.Description=Simulates async page loading over the 530-record GIS source while keeping the same grid surface.
Example.Hierarchy.Title=Hierarchy
Example.Hierarchy.Description=Expands municipalities into lazily loaded feature rows so the same grid can demonstrate tree navigation and child paging.
Example.MasterDetail.Title=Master-Detail
Example.MasterDetail.Description=Shows category master rows that expand into detail headers and lazily loaded GIS feature records.
Example.Personalization.Title=Personalization
Example.Personalization.Description=Combines search, chooser-driven column visibility and saved named views so users can shape the GIS surface at runtime.
Example.ExportImport.Title=Export / Import
Example.ExportImport.Description=Exports the current visible GIS view to CSV and imports a sample CSV back into the live grid so the result set changes immediately.
Example.SummaryDesigner.Title=Summary Designer
Example.SummaryDesigner.Description=Lets the user compose summary chips by choosing a column and aggregate type, then applies the result immediately to the live grid footer.
Example.ActiveLayerSelector.Title=Active Layer Selector
Example.ActiveLayerSelector.Description=Shows a portable layer selector with active-layer routing, icon-based GIS capabilities and a show-more list pattern for larger layer stacks.
Example.YamlInputs.Title=Inputs
Example.YamlInputs.Description=Shows the first professional input wave with portable contracts for text inputs and shared chrome.
Example.YamlPrimitives.Title=Primitives
Example.YamlPrimitives.Description=Shows reusable YAML UI badge and button primitives rendered with Skia chrome and connected to Core through UniversalInput.
Example.YamlDocument.Title=Document
Example.YamlDocument.Description=Shows the first WPF document renderer with nested layout primitives, text fields and footer actions built on the shared runtime document model.
Example.YamlActions.Title=YamlActions
Example.YamlActions.Description=Focuses on the shared document action strip in WPF so we can iterate on action button ergonomics and visual quality.
Example.YamlGenerateForm.Title=Generate form
Example.YamlGenerateForm.Description=Lets the user paste YAML, generate a form from it, and inspect the action result after pressing OK or Cancel.
