ApplicationStateManager.Intro.Title=Shared user-owned UI state, not base definitions
ApplicationStateManager.Intro.Description=This page uses the same shared ApplicationStateManager instance as the rest of the demo. It registers a rendered grid by a stable StateKey, restores persisted layout on load and saves only the user-owned UI overlay.
ApplicationStateManager.Responsibilities.Title=ApplicationStateManager is responsible for
ApplicationStateManager.OutOfScope.Title=ApplicationStateManager is not responsible for
ApplicationStateManager.Cooperation.Title=Cooperation with DefinitionManager
ApplicationStateManager.Cooperation.Description=The base screen still comes from a definition. Once that definition is resolved and rendered, the shared ApplicationStateManager can register the live grid and persist the user-owned overlay above it.
ApplicationStateManager.LiveSample.Title=Live state sample
ApplicationStateManager.LiveSample.Description=Reorder columns, resize them, sort, group or filter the grid below, then save and restore the persisted overlay. The sample uses its own stable StateKey so it does not overwrite the grid showcase state.
ApplicationStateManager.Field.SharedManager=Shared manager
ApplicationStateManager.Field.StateKey=StateKey
ApplicationStateManager.Field.RestoreBehavior=Restore behavior
ApplicationStateManager.Field.SaveBehavior=Save behavior
ApplicationStateManager.Responsibility.SharedManager=Provide one application-level service that every stateful view can share instead of creating page-local persistence helpers.
ApplicationStateManager.Responsibility.RegisterStatefulUi=Register rendered controls by stable host-owned StateKey values such as Demo/Grid/application-state-manager.
ApplicationStateManager.Responsibility.PersistOverlay=Persist only user-owned overlay data such as column layout, sorting, grouping, filters and related view state.
ApplicationStateManager.OutOfScope.Definitions=Resolving YAML, file or in-memory definitions that describe what the base UI should be.
ApplicationStateManager.OutOfScope.Rules=Owning business rules, process policies or any domain behavior outside view state persistence.
ApplicationStateManager.OutOfScope.Data=Storing backend entities, datasets or other domain data that the UI happens to display.
ApplicationStateManager.Value.SharedManager=DemoApplicationServices.ApplicationStateManager
ApplicationStateManager.Value.RestoreBehavior=The grid registers on load and tries to restore the persisted overlay before the user starts working.
ApplicationStateManager.Value.SaveBehavior=Save, restore and reset all go through the same shared manager instance instead of control-local file logic.
DefinitionManager.Intro.Title=Base definitions, not user state
DefinitionManager.Intro.Description=This page is itself driven by a resolved definition. The manager answers what the definition is, where it came from and how a consumer uses it to build the initial UI shape before any user overlay is applied.
DefinitionManager.Responsibilities.Title=DefinitionManager is responsible for
DefinitionManager.OutOfScope.Title=DefinitionManager is not responsible for
DefinitionManager.Resolution.Title=Resolved page definition
DefinitionManager.Resolution.Description=The page asks the shared manager for a semantic key. The returned resolution contains the key, the source and the typed definition payload used to populate the view.
DefinitionManager.Sample.Title=Sample definition consumed by the demo
DefinitionManager.Sample.Description=The second panel resolves a different definition key. The demo uses that payload to render a small preview card and to explain how a screen definition remains the base layer under user-owned application state.
DefinitionManager.Field.DefinitionKey=Definition key
DefinitionManager.Field.Source=Source
DefinitionManager.Field.Kind=Definition kind
DefinitionManager.Field.Component=Component
DefinitionManager.Field.Consumer=Consumer
DefinitionManager.Field.StateOverlay=Application state overlay
DefinitionManager.Page.Responsibility.Resolve=Resolve typed definitions by stable semantic keys such as demo.grid.grouping.
DefinitionManager.Page.Responsibility.ExplainSource=Expose where the definition came from by carrying the source id with the resolved result.
DefinitionManager.Page.Responsibility.BuildBaseUi=Provide the base description used to build or configure a page before user state is applied.
DefinitionManager.Page.OutOfScope.State=Persisting filters, column widths or other user-owned overlays.
DefinitionManager.Page.OutOfScope.Rules=Owning business rules, process policies or financial logic.
DefinitionManager.Page.OutOfScope.Data=Storing backend entities or the live dataset itself.
DefinitionManager.Page.ConsumerHint=This page resolves demo.definition-manager and uses the returned payload to configure its own explanation surface.
DefinitionManager.Page.StateBoundary=ApplicationStateManager may later persist how the rendered page was arranged, but it never owns the base definition.
DefinitionManager.Grouping.Responsibility.Grouping=Defines the default grouping intent and the basic screen metadata for the grouping showcase.
DefinitionManager.Grouping.Responsibility.Columns=Defines the screen identity and core column story that a consumer can use to configure the page.
DefinitionManager.Grouping.OutOfScope.State=The user can still change filters, sorting or widths later, but those overlays are not part of the definition.
DefinitionManager.Grouping.ConsumerHint=A demo page can resolve demo.grid.grouping and use it to decide which screen to render and how to describe it.
DefinitionManager.Grouping.StateBoundary=ApplicationStateManager can persist user tweaks on top of this screen after the page is already built from the definition.
DefinitionManager.ApplicationState.Responsibility.UiState=ApplicationStateManager owns user-specific UI overlay state.
DefinitionManager.ApplicationState.OutOfScope.Definitions=ApplicationStateManager does not resolve the base definition itself.
DefinitionManager.ApplicationState.ConsumerHint=The state manager registers rendered controls by StateKey after the definition has already been resolved.
DefinitionManager.ApplicationState.StateBoundary=Definitions describe the base screen. Application state persists only user changes layered on top.
